&lt;h2&gt;Take your first backup&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="take-your-first-backup"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#take-your-first-backup" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now that your profiles are all set up, you can test your configuration with &lt;code&gt;resticprofile -c ~/profiles.yaml --name &amp;lt;backup-profile-name&amp;gt; backup --dry-run&lt;/code&gt;. Using &lt;code&gt;--dry-run&lt;/code&gt; will show you any issues the backup might encounter, like permission errors or invalid syntax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you do not see any errors, run it again without &lt;code&gt;--dry-run&lt;/code&gt; to take your first backup. You can see your backups with &lt;code&gt;resticprofile -c ~/profiles.yaml --name &amp;lt;backup-profile-name&amp;gt; snapshots&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>